@NODE "Is" "AmigaDOS For Beginners - Read Me First!! - What AmigaDOS For Beginners IS"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS

WHAT AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS IS@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}

@{B}What "AmigaDOS For Beginners" IS:-@{UB}

What "AmigaDOS For Beginners" attempts to do is to provide the beginner
with an introduction to the use of AmigaDOS by providing information and
examples of the AmigaDOS commands in a way that takes the user through
various commands and their main options without getting too tied up in
their @{"format and template" LINK "ADB:Misc/Glossary/Format"}. In my experience, most beginners cannot quickly
understand the formats and templates given in texts about AmigaDOS. By
following through these notes, it is hoped that the beginner can become
familiar with the main options of most commands without needing to worry
too much about formats and templates.

So... whereas I may not always give you the @{B}FULL@{UB} story about an AmigaDOS
command all in the one article I @{B}WILL@{UB} attempt to cover it all by the time
you have read through to the last article. However, if you want the full
story all at once, all you need to do is double click on the highlighted
references to follow through to later articles and read the whole story.


@{JCENTER}=== End of Text ===
@{JLEFT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Not" "AmigaDOS For Beginners - Read Me First!! - What AmigaDOS For Beginners Is NOT"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS

WHAT AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS IS NOT@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}

@{B}"AmigaDOS For Beginners" is NOT@{UB} a replacement for the AmigaDOS manual.

While every AmigaDOS @{"command" LINK "ADB:Misc/Glossary/Commands"} is covered, "AmigaDOS For Beginners" is @{B}not@{UB}
intended to be a @{B}full and definitive@{UB} description of the @{"format or template" LINK "ADB:Misc/Glossary/Format"}
of all these commands. If you want that sort of thing then read the
AmigaDOS manual.


@{JCENTER}=== End of Text ===
@{JLEFT}
@ENDNODE


